 Shiâ€™ites leader in Nigeria, Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky, has arrived Delhi, Indian capital, for medical treatment. As reported by the Channels TV, El-Zakzaky was received by a medical team who conveyed him in a wheelchair to the hospital. El-Zakzaky departed Nigeria at about 6:30 pm on Monday aboard an Emirate flight, with a brief stopover in Dubai. El-Zakzaky and his wife made a stopover at Dubai International Airport at about 4:00 am on Tuesday, and arrived India the same day, Channels TV quoted the spokesperson of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria as saying. 